Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

== Roasted Carrots ==

While rice cooks, trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and halve @Cucumber{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); slice crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick half-moons. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Umami Ginger Meatballs ==

While carrots roast, in a #large bowl{}, gently combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, 1 TBSP @Umami Ginger Sauce{1/2%cup}, @salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Form into 10 1½-inch meatballs.

Arrange meatballs on a second lightly oiled baking sheet. Roast on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Umami Ponzu Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Ponzu Sauce{12%milliliters}, remaining umami ginger sauce, and 1 TBSP @Rice Wine Vinegar{1/2%tablespoon}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until warmed through, ~{60-90%seconds}.

> TIP: If you like a sweeter sauce, stir in a pinch of sugar from your pantry.

== Cucumber Salad ==

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, remaining @Rice Wine Vinegar{1/2%tablespoon}, @Sugar{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Serve rice, roasted carrots, umami ginger meatballs, cucumber salad, umami ponzu sauce, Sriracha mayo, cilantro, and @Crispy Fried Onions{1} family style and let everyone build their own plate.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.